snippet: The Jets’ new general manager will have the autonomy to improve certain areas, like the quarterback mess and eroded talent, but will not be able to change coaches, not at first.
abstract: New York Jets begin interviewing candidates to replace general manager Mike Tannenbaum; next general manager will have autonomy to improve certain areas, like the quarterback mess and eroded talent, but will not be able to replace coach Rex Ryan, at least initially.
lead_paragraph: The Jets’ new general manager will have the autonomy to improve certain areas, like the quarterback mess and eroded talent, but will not be able to change coaches, not at first.

headline.seo: New General Manager Will Inherit Jets’ Chaos, Plus Rex Ryan
headline.main: New G.M. Will Inherit Jets’ Chaos, Plus Coach
